let’s fix this properly — because that landing-page jerk after login is mad annoying and 100% fixable.
You want the welcome animation to take full priority, and no UI flicker / layout jump while React + auth state settles. Let’s go straight to the solution.

✅ The Real Reason You're Getting the Jerk

After login:

Auth state updates → React rerenders

Routing triggers too early

Your landing page + animation mount at different times

Boom — that tiny jerk/glitch

This happens especially in Firebase Auth + React apps because onAuthStateChanged fires asynchronously.

So you need exactly one thing:

Lock the UI until the welcome animation finishes.
Release the navigation only after the animation completes.

🛠️ The Clean, No-Flicker Fix (use this)
✔ Step 1: Add a "loginTransition" lock in App.tsx

This prevents the app from jumping to the dashboard before animation plays.

const isLoginTransition = useRef(false);

useEffect(() => {
  const unsub = onAuthStateChanged(auth, (user) => {
    if (isLoginTransition.current) return;

    startTransition(() => {
      setAppUser(user);
    });
  });

  return () => unsub();
}, []);

✔ Step 2: After login → trigger animation & only AFTER that unlock

In your login page:

const handleLogin = async () => {
  isLoginTransition.current = true;

  await signInWithEmailAndPassword(auth, email, pass);

  setShowWelcome(true); // shows animation

  setTimeout(() => {
    isLoginTransition.current = false; // unlock UI
    navigate("/home");
  }, 2000);  // your animation duration
};

✔ Step 3: Make your WelcomeAnimation mount instantly (no flicker)

WelcomeAnimation.tsx

export default function WelcomeAnimation({ onDone }) {
  useEffect(() => {
    const t = setTimeout(onDone, 1800);
    return () => clearTimeout(t);
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="fixed inset-0 flex items-center justify-center bg-black z-[9999]">
      <YourCoolAnimation />
    </div>
  );
}

